summaries.short: Series Premiere. A multiracial family shows some of its cracks as the father's 60th birthday party approaches.
summaries.full: Series Premiere. As Audrey Bayer puts the finishing touches on her husband Greg's 60th birthday party--a milestone Greg is loath to celebrate--cracks begin to emerge in their progressive, multiracial family.

summaries.short: Ramon and Shokrani explore a psychic connection; Kristen and Ashley run afoul of the law.
summaries.full: Ramon and Shokrani explore the possible psychic connection between '11:11' and a photograph in the doctor's office. Kristen and Ashley run into trouble. Duc gets good news about his self-help manuscript, but his mood is dampened by the publisher's request. Audrey is enlisted to help break up a politically incorrect new society at school.

summaries.short: Greg gets detoured on the way to an ethics convention; Audrey is thrust in the media spotlight.
summaries.full: Greg gets detoured in the wilderness on the way to an ethics convention. Audrey finds herself in the media crosshairs after a hate crime at school. After a mountain-bike race with best-friend Malcolm and their pals, Duc reveals the secret to staying in control, a credo that's tested by a fellow life coach named Carmen.

summaries.short: Greg and Audrey look for funding; Layla bristles over Farid's behavior; Haley has a birthday party.
summaries.full: Greg and Audrey look to the past to find financing for the Empathy Initiative. Kristen is partnered with Navid, Farid's son, in a school project, and learns there's more to him than meets the eye. Farid debates Islam with the mosque's Imam, much to Layla's chagrin. The family heads to a familiar retreat to celebrate Haley's birthday, with an unexpected conclusion.
